OL,3,CWhy the welfare reform row is about so
OL,4,Cmuch more than welfare
OL,6,FThey don't ask why a Labour government
OL,7,Frespects the OBR, especially after the
OL,8,FTruss/Kwarteng fiscal debacle caused
OL,9,Fby their disrespect for the OBR.
OL,11,FBut they do question why the
OL,12,FChancellor and Treasury endow the OBR
OL,13,Fwith an almost mystical ability to
OL,14,Fdetermine which policies are sensible,
OL,15,Fand why Reeves has seemingly abdicated
OL,16,Fresponsibility for trying to sell the
OL,17,Fgovernment's initiatives to the
OL,18,Fcountry's creditors independently of
OL,19,Fthe OBR and fiscal rules straitjacket.
